---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Hot Water Hampton Park | Gas, Heat-Pump, Solar, Same-Day Repairs | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Hot water specialists in Hampton Park — same-day repairs, gas / heat-pump / solar / electric replacements. Hampton Park 3976, older established estates, ageing gas storage replacements. Solar Vic rebate. VBA-licensed."
  canonical="https://sehotwater.com.au/hampton-park/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Hampton Park 3976 &middot; Established 1980s&ndash;90s estates</span>
      <h1>Hot water in <span class="accent">Hampton Park</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Hampton Park is the most ageing-housing-stock postcode in our service
        area &mdash; 1980s-90s brick veneer with original gas storage tanks
        many of which are now 25&ndash;35 years old. We replace 4&ndash;5 a
        week here. Same-day repairs, sensible upgrade paths, and the $1,000
        Solar Vic rebate handled in-house.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Hampton Park</span>
      <h2>The Hampton Park hot water story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>1980s-90s housing &mdash; mostly original storage tanks still in service.</h3>
        <p>
          Hampton Park was developed predominantly through the 1980s and into
          the early 1990s. Default install of the era was a Rheem Stellar
          170L or Vulcan / Aquaheat 250L gas storage tank externally mounted on
          a concrete pad. Cylinder design life is 10&ndash;12 years &mdash;
          which means most original tanks here have already been replaced once
          (in the 2000s) and the replacements are themselves now nearing or past
          end-of-life. Combined with anode rods that have never been swapped,
          we&rsquo;re seeing a steady stream of corrosion-failure replacements.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Mixed owner-occupier and rental &mdash; affects rebate eligibility.</h3>
        <p>
          Hampton Park has a meaningful proportion of rental and investment
          stock. The Solar Vic heat-pump rebate is restricted to
          owner-occupiers. For owner-occupiers, heat-pump conversion is the
          smart play &mdash; net $3K&ndash;$4.5K, ~$500/year saving, 5&ndash;6
          year payback. For rental properties, like-for-like gas replacement
          stays cheapest upfront for the landlord, though Victoria&rsquo;s
          minimum rental standards are tightening on hot water and the
          long-term direction is electrification.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Older gas lines &mdash; watch the upgrade compatibility.</h3>
        <p>
          Some original Hampton Park gas plumbing is 15mm copper sized for a
          modest storage tank. Upgrading to a high-flow Rinnai Infinity 26 may
          need a gas line upsize to 20mm &mdash; we check pressure on site
          before quoting. Likewise, the meter may need to be upsized by the
          gas retailer; we coordinate that.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Hampton Park jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>25+ year old Rheem Stellar 170L &mdash; like-for-like Rinnai HotFlo 170L ($1.9K&ndash;$2.4K)</li>
          <li>Vulcan 250L conversion to Rinnai Infinity 20 instantaneous (gas line check required) &mdash; $2.5K&ndash;$3K</li>
          <li>Gas storage to heat-pump conversion (Reclaim 250L) &mdash; $3.5K&ndash;$4K net after rebates</li>
          <li>Tempering valve replacement (mandatory at 50&deg;C max under AS 3500) &mdash; $300&ndash;$450</li>
          <li>Same-day pilot light + thermocouple repair &mdash; $200&ndash;$400</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other South East service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/south-east-melbourne/">All South East Melbourne</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Hampton Park hot water quote.</h2>
        <p>Tired old tank? Quote within 24 hours. Same-day if urgent.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
